    <docTitle>Lehigh Valley Railroad Telegram</docTitle>
    <headnote>Telegraph sent June 20, 1903 to confirm maintenance performed on batteries on turntable at South
        Easton, LVRR. Found loose, with initial request attached, at Golden Nugget flea market, Titusville NJ, summer 2018.
        Collection of C. R. Chinoy.</headnote>
    <docText>
        <header>
        <form rr="LVRR" formNo="64" formRev="1902-04-24">Form 64 4-24-1902</form>
        <title>LEHIGH VALLEY RAILROAD</title>
        <subtitle>TELEGRAM</subtitle>
        <operator>Bm</operator>
        <itemDate dateFrom="1903-06-20">6/20/03</itemDate>
        <salutation>Mr J Haskey,</salutation>
        </header>
        <body><p>
            The <equipt>batteries on the Gaso. Engine</equipt><br/>
            <equipt><place>So. Easton turn table</place></equipt> and on the <br/>
            <equipt>bank ball <!--crc: "bank ball" refers to an electrically lit or operated ball-type signal, in this case, a banking
            signal, i.e. for a siding used for operation of helper locomotives--></equipt> at <place>Bethlehem</place> were fixed <br/>
            up &amp; reported working OK by <person class="employee" who="RenshawB.S.">B.S. <br/>
            Reushaw</person> yesterday </p></body>
        <footer><signature><person class="employee" who="GersbachJ.P.">J P Gersbach</person></signature> <operator>Ru</operator></footer>
    </docText>
